description: For sale: $425,000. This coveted Tangletown location in Mac Groveland is steps from restaurants, bookstores and coffee shops on Grand Avenue. Inside you are welcomed with hardwood floors, a wood burning fireplace surrounded with built-ins, and lots of light.  The main floor includes a large dining area and cheerful kitchen with pantry. Upstairs there are 3 bedrooms, including a spacious master. The upstairs sun porch is perfect for a nap, meditation or reading a book. The lower level provides versatile space for a game room or exercise. The laundry room includes a ¾ bath and a sauna! You will find this lovely home just two blocks from Macalester College.  Showings begin Friday 4/17.  Check out the virtual 360 degree tour in the meantime!

For sale: $475,000. Beautifully updated home in popular Mac-Groveland neighborhood. Charming enclosed front porch. Open main level; great for entertaining. Hardwood floors. Living room with cozy fireplace. Informal dining room. Bright open kitchen with granite counters & snack bar. French doors leading to two bedrooms on the main level and a full bath. Upper level private master suite with full bath & 2 walk-in closets. Finished lower level with family room. 4th bedroom & 3/4 bath. New Roof 2017. New Boiler 2019. New Ductless Mini-Split AC/Heat 2016. New Patio and Landscaping 2016. New Wood Fence in the backyard 2015. Blocks from the river and walking distance to the shops and restaurants of Highland Village. Move-in ready!

For sale: $729,900. Welcome to Crocus Hill's Finest New Listing. Amazing attention to detail on this newly completed remodel of this Colonial Home Offering an Abundance of Living Space. 100% complete remodel both inside and out.  Newly Added 2-Story Addition offers both a Private Master Suite, Upstairs Laundry and Stunning Main Floor Kitchen. Master Bath Features Free Standing Tub, Seperate Shower, Walk-in Closet and Dual Vanities. You'll love all the new upgraded finishes throughout the home and the historic charm. Custom Remodel Includes: Floor to Ceiling Amish Cabinetry with Soft Close, Rollout Garbage, Custom Black Walnut Island Top, Quartz Countertops, Farmhouse Sinks, Brand New SS Appliances and Washer and Dryer, Main Floor Mudroom w/Lockers and Powder Bath, Anderson Windows, New Roof, Matching Doors and Trim to Original Vintage of Home. 4 Bedrooms Upstairs and Lots of Storage in Lower Level.

description: For sale: $475,000. Classic 1920's home conveniently located in Mac Groveland a block from Mattock's park. Lovely spaces and details in this home- hardwood floors, crown molding with picture rail, built-ins, and upper level with 4 bedrooms and charming bath. The kitchen features stainless steel appliances and flows seamlessly into the spacious main-floor family room. Enjoy the 2-car garage and inviting backyard patio.

Coming soon: $124,900. One-level condo living at Wilder Park conveniently located near Grand Avenue for easy access to shops and restaurants. Stunning 12th floor views of downtown skyline and area parks where you can watch baseball in the Summer and hockey in the Winter. Updates throughout with vinyl plank flooring, bathroom cabinets, customized cut-out tub, and stainless-steel appliances. Unit includes heated underground parking stall with option to rent second stall and access to countless amenities including workout facilities, garden plots, party rooms, and more! Don?t miss our 3D virtual tour!
For more information on this listing before it goes on the market, please reach out to our Listing Manager, Laurie Jones, at laurie@kerbyandcristina.com.

For sale: $579,000. Location, Location, Location!
Gorgeous two level condo with three full baths, Fireplace, giant finished rec room/sleeping area, lots of storage, two car attached garage, large laundry room/workshop, grand tall ceilings throughout both levels of condo, 1893 charm with many original features and fully renovated in 2018. A unique Private entry home/ front and back deck on Summit / and a 20 second walk to Grand Ave action!  With all new renovations and carefree condo living you can relax and enjoy the vibrant neighborhood. H20, Garbage, Lawn care, Snow Removal all included with the condo association. Option to acquire with all furnishings/floor rugs.

For sale: $999,000. Handsome, 3 story Tudor w/slate roof, outstanding curb appeal and beautiful lot, on a prestigious block of Mississippi River Blvd. Soak up the sun year round in a glorious solarium, kitchen and family room addition. Classic main floor with lovely foyer, generously sized living and dining rooms, sunroom/study, many period touches, fireplace, reading nooks and lots of windows. 3 bedrooms on second floor, one with a private balcony overlooking the award winning garden. Master bedroom has a walk in closet and 3/4 bath. Third floor has a sweet bedroom, full bath, and generous attic. There are 2 staircases to the lower level, one leads to a finished recreation room with full windows, 1/2 bath and an adjoining study. The other staircase to the laundry and mechanicals. Gorgeous setting on one of the premiere blocks of Mississippi River Blvd.

description: For sale: $375,000. Contact the listing agent, Krista Wolter, at 612-247-5106 for additional information and a private showing. Welcome home to this Story Book Charmer on Lincoln Avenue in St. Paul! This home is on a wonderful block near the river and has easy access to trails, shopping and restaurants. Step inside to find newly refinished hardwood floors and steps to bedrooms upstairs. Sunroom on main floor off dining room. Eat-in kitchen has lots of built-in cabinetry for extra storage. Unfinished lower level. Spacious backyard and 2 car garage. Ready to move in and enjoy this summer!

Coming soon: $699,900. Charming duplex now available! This is a turn key, one-of-a-kind gem that is move-in ready. Home has been meticulously maintained top to bottom including all utilities and mechanicals.  Incredible craftsmanship and design throughout entire home. Large floor plans, beautiful woodwork, updated kitchens and bathrooms, large bedrooms and living spaces. 2 sets of washer/dryers, separate utilities & mechanicals. Many updated 3 pane windows. Newer built massive insulated 4 car, commercial grade garage, with 3 steel roll up doors. Macalester  Groveland location is fantastic, walking/biking distance to shops, groceries, colleges, coffee, parks and more. This home is a MUST SEE in a MUST HAVE neighborhood. Home won't last long, don't wait!

For sale: $759,000. Located in the heart of St. Paul on Grand Avenue, just steps from local coffee shops, restaurants and grocery stores. Each unit is spacious and functional, not to mention upscale and extremely sophisticated. The Union on Grand condos are an appropriate mix of modern comforts and interior finishes with a vintage-like aesthetic, giving each residence a classic loft vibe. Each of the remaining two units come with two parking spaces as well!

For sale: $325,000. Looking for a new home to "shelter in place'?  This sweet Mac-Groveland two story has been well cared for by the same owner for more than 50 years. From the planter boxes to the porch this one is a cutie! Offering a spacious living and dining room with true character of the original woodwork, fireplace and built-ins. Stunning hardwood floors throughout, lovely solid wood doors and some updates.  Three nicely sized bedrooms up with full bath.  Newer Ikea kitchen cabinets and a half bath on the main brings good function to this home.  With a flat corner lot, you have plenty of outdoor entertaining space as well. The garage offers the space of a two car + loft above with separate entrance competes the need for additional storage or play space. Not wanting to hang out at home???  The walkability of this location has some much to offer, all it needs is you!

description: For sale: $208,000. Check out the 3D tour. Come and see this 2 bed, 1 bath condo on the famous Grand Avenue, this home is full of charm. From the wood burning fireplace to the stained-glass windows, you'll feel right at home. This unit comes with a deeded parking spot that is steps away from the gated entrance to the building and a LARGE storage unit in the basement for all your extra things. It also has a brand-new kitchen with granite countertops, stainless steel appliances, a large farm sink, and a sparkling back splash. There is in-unit laundry in the master bedroom that offers great convenience. The full bathroom is newly updated with a marble vanity top and a new toilet. There is also access to the deck from the condo where you can enjoy the weather during the warmer months. The brand-new kitchen has an eat-in peninsula, but there is room for a full table in the living/dining area as well. This home has an unbeatable walk score to all sorts of shops and restaurants. All appliances included.

description:
For sale: $389,000. This is what you have been waiting for, Mac Groveland's American Bungalow style home featuring 4 bedrooms, 2 baths, and a 2 car garage.
Some of the features include a remodel of the 4-season porch complete with new windows and French door that allows you to access the fenced in yard with large brick patio.  Bathroom remodel has a heated marble tile floor, Restoration Hardware sink and faucets, and a rain shower head.  Almost all of the lighting has been updated throughout the home with Schoolhouse Electric, Pottery Barn, and Restoration hardware fixtures.  The Living Room has a wood burning fireplace with a heat-efficient Aaron's insert.  Kitchen boasts high end stainless appliances, quartz countertops, and a design that utilizes the space efficiently.  Location Location Location, within walking distance to Groveland Park and Elementary school and just 4 blocks south of Grand Ave.  Don't wait!

description: For sale: $309,900. Rare opportunity for a stunning craftsman home with refinished hardwood floors, built-in buffet in dining room, built-in bench next to brick fireplace & newer kitchen. Updated kitchen with classic white cabinetry and newer stainless appliances. 3 BRs on the upper level including two with walk-in closets. Opportunity to add a 4th BR to the finished LL. Brand new high-end washer & dryer set. Upper-level tiled bathroom with brand new vanity, mirror & exhaust fan. Fenced yard with 6' tall chain link fence and useful storage shed attached to the garage! New 3/4 or full bathroom in lower level could be added prior to closing.ABOVE list price.

For sale: $350,000. Wonderful St. Paul Crocus Hill Condo with outdoor space. Beautiful Hardwood Floors, claw foot tub, wainscoting, molding and exposed brick make this unit incredibly charming. Freshly painted master suite, custom radiator covers with bookshelves above and a great updated kitchen. All rooms are large and open. Master suite includes a huge den/office with wood burning fireplace. Wonderful front porch is the perfect space for outdoor living, morning coffee or evening hangout. Top floor location. No neighbors overhead. In-unit laundry. Stairs only. 1 car garage. Grand Ave/Dale so close to shopping, restaurants and public transportation. This is a must see!

description: For sale: $424,500. Been dreaming of living in Mac Groveland with the dream home AND dream garage? Then this hard to find craftsman bungalow charmer is what you've been waiting for! Proudly situated on a beautiful corner lot and full of character and charm, this home has original woodwork, built-ins, fireplace and box beam ceilings that will more than impress. The home boasts 4 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, and over 2,000 finished square feet. An incomparable two-story garage has approx. 500 square feet of finishing opportunity for an office, studio, den, you name it - add equity! Plus the garage also has a main floor full length workshop for your projects and hobbies. Walk to restaurants and shops on Grand Avenue and enjoy all that Mac Groveland and Summit Hill neighborhoods have to offer. This kind of opportunity doesn't come along often!

For sale: $600,000. Safety and health are our top priority. We are available to show this home virtually and the Seller is allowing for individual showings. description: For sale: $549,900. Spacious and sophisticated condo in Saint Paul's sought-after Waldorf Flats. A recent award-winning renovation maintained the architectural details of the original Hermann Kretz Georgian Revival design, while creating fully up-to-date and spacious interiors in each of its two buildings. A gracious and open flow includes a living room with gas fireplace, dining room with exposed brick wall, a modern open kitchen with soapstone countertops and stainless steel appliances, and a conveniently located laundry/mudroom with separate access.  Both bedrooms feature ensuite bathrooms with upgraded countertops and stylish fixtures. Beautiful hardwood floors, newly upgraded carpeting, many windows, central AC, and a covered balcony overlooking historic Summit Avenue. Amenities include: Security system, amazing exercise room, and garage parking.

description: For sale: $335,000. Located in desirable Mac-Grove, this newly renovated home offers you all the original charm, with those modern conveniences you just can't live without.  Gleaming 100 year old hardwood floors and coved ceilings greet you. The large windows allow for an abundance of natural light.  The fully modern kitchen with granite counter tops, custom cabinetry, and stainless steel appliances overlook the dining area and original, preserved oak buffet.  Hardwood floors continue throughout the main level's 2 bedrooms.  Upstairs provides an additional 2 bedrooms and a brand new ½ bath.  Price does include outside landscaping of front and back yard that will be completed once the weather allows.  This one won't last long!

For sale: $479,900. Nestled in the desirable Macalester-Groveland neighborhood, this home is only a few short blocks away from the river. Tastefully appointed kitchen with gorgeous granite counter tops, recessed lighting, and pass through access leading to the formal dining, living and family room is ideal for entertaining as well as everyday life. The formal living offers large windows allowing plenty of natural light, fireplace, natural woodwork and arched doorways. The oversized main level family room as beautifully built in cabinetry and hardwood flooring. The second level has four spacious bedrooms, a full bath and a private 3/4 master bath. The lower level has bonus space ideal for a game room or a second family room.

description: For sale: $1,375,000. A stunning architectural treasure updated for today's needs. This elegant home offers you grand, gracious,  comfortable living with generous room sizes, unsurpassed architectural detail, and an updated kitchen fitted with high-end European appliances.  Four bedrooms and two bathrooms are on the second floor, including the original master bedroom and master bath.  The entire third floor is now a luxury master suite that includes a master bath with both a claw foot tub and a walk-in shower, a washer and dryer, ample closets and lots of storage. A rare three-car garage offers space for all your vehicles and toys.  The spacious back yard is private and fully fenced and dotted with mature pine trees. Check out the video tour in the supplements!

For sale: $650,000. Many family gatherings have occurred over the last 50 years at this charming Crocus Hill home. Lovely woodwork, newly refinished hardwood floors, fresh interior paint, spacious rooms, newer kitchen and baths and a dbl garage with storage room and bath. Buyers will need to do some updating. This is a wonderful opportunity to buy in Crocus Hill. A lot split has been approved by the county. This home would be on a 60x150ft lot. Buyers may purchase the easterly lot(40x150).

description: For sale: $1,250,000. Located in the original Hill District, this stunning 1908 Summit Avenue home boasts the design by Sundburg and constructed by Carl P. Walden. The combination of both centuries creates spacious entertaining spaces, gourmet kitchen with Thermador refrigerator & in-island beverage drawers, breathtaking living & dining room, updated bathrooms with in-floor heat, 3 fireplaces, club room, impressive master suite with en suite closet/dressing room & retreat, library, wine cellar, sauna/spa, grand entertaining 3 season porch, mud room, office and 3rd floor get away. Walk out the front door and enjoy majestic Summit Avenue, walk out the back door and enjoy all Grand Avenue has to offer!

description: For sale: $749,900. Sun-filled Summit Ave 4BR/3.5BA home perfectly blends historic charm & modern updates! Large south-facing corner lot on quiet stretch of Saint Paul's most sought after street. Step from large foyer/entry into sunny living room with gas FP, original moldings, bookshelves & built-ins. Gorgeous bifold French doors lead to adjacent sun room/study. Exceptional formal DR w/built-ins, wainscoting, & original hand-painted mural. Custom eat-in kitchen boasts corian countertops, marble backsplash & dual-element 5 burner range. Step through French doors from kitchen to screened porch overlooking the backyard for indoor/outdoor living. Spacious master w/connected updated 3/4 bath. 3 additional BR's & full bath on 2nd floor. 3rd floor rec room perfect for kids or studio. LL includes finished main area ample storage, tool room, large laundry room & 1/2 bath. Water heater 2017. Steps to all Grand Ave has to offer & a view of the Summit Islands! Easy access to HWY 94, both downtowns & the airport.

description: For sale: $1,295,000. Welcome home to this stunning 1924 English Tudor. Character, charm and  craftsmanship describe this superb generational home - one that only becomes available every 20-30 years. Timeless original touches include arched ceilings, sweeping staircases, & leaded glass windows & doors, and are tastefully combined with many modern upgrades and amenities making it ideal for families & entertainers alike. Features include gourmet kitchen with eat-in area designed for a chef that loves to entertain, spacious living and family rooms with architectural details and wood fireplace, basement family room with wood fireplace, terrazzo floor, and bar. 2nd level has recently refinished floors. Outdoor areas include a picture-perfect backyard with new double patio and perennial gardens plus a 3-season front porch. Enjoy plentiful storage throughout the home.  The attached 2-car garage is a rarity on Summit Avenue.  Walk to many shops & restaurants in this ultra-convenient and highly-desirable location.
Zestimate® Home Value: $263,912. This 868 square foot single family home has 2 bedrooms and 1.0 bathrooms. It is located at 337 Brimhall St Saint Paul, Minnesota.

description: For sale: $2,195,000. Welcome to this exquisite Mediterranean inspired estate on St. Paul's prestigious Mississippi River Boulevard. Situated on a rare double lot the remarkable fully landscaped grounds will not disappoint. The custom pool and surrounding patios are perfect for enjoying the river views and stunning sunsets. The Interior and exterior architectural details have been meticulously maintained for nearly a century. Features include huge sun-filled spaces, a designer chef's dream kitchen with Center Island that opens to the informal dining space and family room. The gracious foyer leads to the living room and dining room both with massive river view windows. There is beautiful red oak hardwood flooring throughout, and three wood burning fireplaces. Upstairs you will find the bedrooms including the luxurious master suite with its private changing area and bath. The river road lifestyle offers miles of hiking, biking, walking, and running trails. This is truly a once in a lifetime opportunity.

For sale: $799,900. Classic Summit Avenue Tudor. Oversized, private lot, perennial gardens. Remarkable full front porch for summer living. Light-filled main floor family room addition, four beds and two baths on 2nd level, plus a sleeping porch. Third level oversized Owner's Suite with room for sitting area, multiple closets, morning balcony, separate tub and steam shower. Original alley garage is ready to be converted to an accessory dwelling unit, if permitted. Attached garage is oversized. Unfinished basement has many windows and opportunity.

For sale: $2,295,000. This stately red granite Crocus Hill home was built by Frank B. Kellogg, former US Secretary State and recipient of the Nobel Peace Prize. The 9000 square foot mansion features breathtaking interiors, inlaid and pegged floors, 1/2 acre lot with reflection pool, carriage house, stunning 2004 renovation and was a Showcase home by the American Society of Interior Designers (ASID) and is a designated National Historic Landmark.

description: Recently sold: $460,000. Meticulously updated 4BR/3BA home in PRIME Mac/Groveland location! Hardwood floors, crown molding and custom wainscoting provide tons of character and charm. Upstairs, you'll find the expansive owner's suite with luxury bathroom and beautiful feature wall. In the finished lower level, you'll want to curl up with a good book in front of the large stone fireplace (gas) with custom hearth, or for enjoy the in-ceiling surround sound theater. No expense was spared on the gorgeous exterior renovations which include James Hardie siding, custom stonework, LeafGuard gutters, newer windows and more. Enjoy entertaining in the amazing, private backyard featuring a massive paver patio with custom cedar pergola, 6' cedar privacy fence and impeccable landscaping complete w/landscape lighting. The updated 2-car garage features new LP SmartSide siding, new windows and service door, the backyard shed is perfect for storing all your toys and tools. This home is ready to go and priced to sell fast.

description: Recently sold: $325,000. Classic gem in highly desirable Mac/Groveland just one block from Grand Avenue. In addition to the amazing location this home boasts loads of charm and character to include great curb appeal, a lovely open front porch, beautiful hardwood floors, cozy wood burning fireplace, original banister, stained glass window, built in buffet and bookshelves, eat in kitchen, new garage, beautiful landscaping and back yard deck for entertaining. With a few updates this could be your dream home!

Recently sold: $420,000. Sundrenched condo in the heart of Crocus Hill with spectacular southern views. Directly across the street from Linwood Park and Linwood Community Center. Beautiful woodwork, gleaming floors. Updated kitchen with bosch dishwasher & granite as well as updated baths. Newer gas fireplace to warm you on those chilly evenings! Watch the 4th of July fireworks from the comfort of your sunroom! Only blocks from Victoria & Grand...one of St. Paul's most desirable shopping/dining destinations! Bus stops directly out the front door for easy commute. Great walkable neighborhood as well as convenience to major highways. Just a quick 15 minutes to the airport! Two 8x10 storage rooms. Seller used one as their private art studio. In unit laundry as well as additional laundry in lower level. Move in and enjoy all that this neighborhood has to offer!

description: Recently sold: $321,000. Welcome home to this Storybook Charmer that has been in the same family for 78 years!  It features newly finished hardwood floors, gas fireplace with brick surround, built-in bookshelves, an updated kitchen with new gas stove and front porch off the living room space.  2 bedrooms on the main floor with one that has been used as a den that includes built-in desk, file drawers and shelving.  Spacious, upstairs bedroom with den area, plenty of of closets and could easily house a 3rd bathroom for it to become the perfect master suite. Fenced back yard. Newer water heater and brand new furnace as of November 2019. Convenient location close to Nativity. Ready to move in and enjoy!

Recently sold: $440,000. Large 2 Bed+Office/Den, 1 Bath Apartment- GREAT GRAND AVE LOCATION! Available June 1! - This lower level, large apartment features beautiful hardwood floors throughout! The spacious living room/dining room opens to an office/den (3rd room) with french doors and lots of natural light. The hardwood floors continue down the hall and into both bedrooms. A 4th room (also perfect as another office or den) is located off the bedrooms. Multiple closets in unit provide excellent storage. Over 1500 sqft in this unit!

Excellent location on the corner of Grand Ave and Albert St- near Kowalski's Market! Detached 2-car garage available for an additional charge. All essential utilities included. Cats allowed with deposit, no dogs. Available 
June 1st!

Note: This property does not participate in the Section 8 program.

No Dogs Allowed

(RLNE5458380)

description:
Recently sold: $275,000. Beautiful Highland Park Home for rent! Gorgeous hardwood floors throughout the main level of this home, with a bright kitchen and eat-in area. Living room, dining room, bath and kitchen are located on the main floor. Three bedrooms and bathroom are located on the upper level. Laundry and open space are in the lower level. Air conditioning and a separate two car garage. Beautiful new fence around the backyard. 

Great location blocks from public transport -- minutes away from Highland Park boutiques, Macalester College, St. Kate's, St. Thomas, Concordia and Hamline; MSP Airport, MOA and Highland Park public golf course. Exceptional quality in a wonderful location! 

We love the location of this home! The neighborhood is incredible, with fantastic neighbors, a sense of community and big trees lining this charming street. The home is "move in ready"!

Owner pays for trash. Tenants care for lawn and snow removal, pay for electricity and water expense.

description:
Recently sold: $310,000. Beautiful home in a great St. Paul location. This home has 4 bedrooms as well as 3 bathrooms. Master room has a ton of built-ins with natural sunlight! All bedrooms have hardwood flooring with closet space. The kitchen gives you a cozy feel featuring a breakfast bar. The living room is very spacious with big windows, perfect for sunny days (or even rainey if you like that)! There is fresh new paint throughout the whole home. You will have your own washer in dryer located in the basement. 1 detached garage stall. School District #625.

Lease Terms: $2295 Security Deposit. Seeking a 12 month lease term or longer. Tenant is responsible for all utilities and snow and lawn care. Pets may be accepted based on the owner's approval and with a $300 non refundable pet fee. This home does not qualify for section 8.

For additional information please use the link below for a YouTube video walkthrough of the home.

Rental Screening Guidelines:
Background and Credit Checks are conducted on all adults
Income of 3x the monthly rent or more
Credit score of 600 or higher (under 600 can be considered with a double deposit)
No felonies or violence related criminal convictions
No previous evictions

The criteria above are not all inclusive and other factors may apply, it is only meant to be a guideline. 
Perfect SFH with fenced in yard!

Recently sold: $1,350,000. Handsome brick 5 bedroom 5 bath home designed by Clarence Johnston with a recent home addition and new kitchen designed by Charlie Simmons and work done by John Kraemer. It offers a delightful open front porch for summer enjoyment, entertainment sized living and dining rooms with hardwood floors and a cozy main floor den with a wood burning fireplace. It features a fabulous new kitchen with large center island, a king sized master bedroom with huge walk in closet and bath, and an amazing game room on 3rd floor that could also be a nanny's quarters with its own kitchen, bath and bedroom. The lower level offers a large amusement/media room, an exercise room and ample storage. The yard is privacy fenced with a heated garage which has a charging port for an electric car.

description: Recently sold: $425,000. Quietly poised on a beautiful street is this true Macalester classic!    Dramatic entry and stunningly preserved natural woodwork!   Generous room sizes throughout.  Cozy gas fireplace in living room. Charming updated kitchen with original butler's pantry.  Main floor powder room.  Full bath remodel including heated floors.  4 bedrooms on one level including a sleeping porch to enjoy on those summer evenings. Finished 3rd level offers flex space.  Beautiful mature gardens and trees all around the home and fully fenced in backyard.   Walk to the river or to all that Historic Grand Avenue has to offer. Listed on Macalaster Groveland Community Council's Century registry for homes over 100 years old.

description: Recently sold: $771,000. Welcome! This is the first time this home has been offered for sale publicly. The current owners are just the fourth owners and have improved the home beautifully while respecting the original design. It is spacious &sunny, yet warm & inviting! The original details such as the stained/leaded glass, box beam ceilings and built in are all still intact yet the floor plan is open! Stunning kitchen designed by Fiddlehead features custom built, inset white  cabinets, a spacious center island and top of the line appliances. The kitchen and three season-porch overlook the private, landscaped yard. The second floor offers four spacious bedrooms & a sunroom. There is also laundry on the 2nd floor & huge closets! The third floor is beautiful master retreat with huge windows, high ceilings, walk in closet & lovely master bath (also plumbed for laundry). The LL is already heated and ready for expansion. The garage also offers room for expansion with the walk-up attic! Think ADU, studio or office!

Upper level is master suite with  full bath.  Main level reflects charm of the era with wood floors, period woodwork and built-ins. Recently sold: $725,000. Lovely home is the perfect mix of historic character and charm with modern conveniences! The fantastic wrap around porch is perfect for morning coffee while inside, the foyer welcomes you with tiny rainbows from leaded windows dancing across the open staircase, freshly finished hardwood floors and crystal chandeliers.  To the right, the family room opens to formal living room with fireplace, book cases and high ceilings.  Sunny dining room features a lovely built in for your china and crystal.  Eat in kitchen with American style  AGA 4x4 range and tile back splash brought from Spain to match.  Second floor has a master with en suite, two additional bedrooms, one with a fireplace, a full bath and great vaulted laundry room.  Third floor is super unique fun space, could be used as 4th bedroom or awesome home office with vaulted ceiling, skylights and treetop writer's nook!  Back yard has amazing pond and water fall, brick patio, tons of perennials and a sweet pergola.

description: Recently sold: $825,775. Built in 2003, this sophisticated and elegant, architecturally designed Crocus Hill home features bright and open spaces, master bedroom suite with fireplace, in-floor heating, exquisite interiors, stunning terrace, quality craftsmanship and artful combination of maintenance free living and classic prairie school design. You will love the contemporary spaces inside and out, all gracefully blended into this charming and historic Saint Paul neighborhood.

Recently sold: $788,000. Beautiful Edwin Lundie home in Tangletown is brimming w/stunning updates, original character, and a landscaped urban oasis in the backyard. Enjoy wonderful millwork around the fireplace in the LR, a spacious DR to hold family and friends, heated flooring in the sunroom w/vaulted wooden ceiling, and a remodeled eat-in kitchen w/honed granite counters and SS appliances. Main level 3/4 bath, office, and mudroom can also be found here. 3 BDs sit upstairs and the 4th BD on the 3rd level. Owner's suite boasts gas fireplace, a den overlooking the lush treetops in the backyard, and a custom 3/4 ensuite bath. LL family room is great for the younger generation! Sip morning coffee in the Zen-like oasis of a backyard while enjoying the bubbling of the waterfall and pond it cascades into. Excellent location close to many delicious restaurants along Grand Ave. Easy commute to either downtown, the MSP airport, as well as many public transportation options. Don't miss your chance to call this home.

description: Recently sold: $303,000.
Recently sold: $359,524.

Recently sold: $289,500. Wonderful home in Mac-Groveland neighborhood! This home lays claim to beautiful refinished hardwood floors, abundant daylight, and spacious living areas! The living and dining rooms welcome you in with coved ceilings, natural woodwork, a gas-burning fireplace, and great areas to entertain. Host large holiday celebrations and intimate gatherings in the generously sized formal dining room. The adjoining den works wonderfully as a home office or sunroom! The kitchen boasts copious cabinetry, lots of counter space, and subway tiled backsplash; it will quickly become the heart of your home. Around the corner from the living areas the two, main-floor bedrooms await. Each offers privacy as they are seemingly tucked away from the rest of the home. The home's full bathroom sits between them for added convenience. The lower level is waiting for your imagination to shape it! With a finished 3/4 bathroom and finished storage room, the addition of a family room would complete this space. Access to the tuck-under, two car garage can be found here; it will keep your cars and toys free from the elements year round. Enjoy walking to nearby restaurants and shops! An easy bike ride brings you to miles of trails along the Mississippi River! Don't miss the chance to call this home.

Recently sold: $363,400. OPEN HOUSE - SATURDAY - JULY 6
Noon to 2 pm
Showing also by appointment.
Contact us by email, text or phone.

Distinctive Dutch Colonial in Saint Paul's Mac-Groveland neighborhood that's gearing up for her 100th anniversary.  A home for the seasons.  Warmer weather moves your living to the huge screened-in porch and provides hours of creative nurturing in your mature garden -- it's lake home living without the drive . . . and the lake (sorry).  When the weather gets cool, the fireplace and family room make for a perfectly cozy retreat.  Original built-ins, oak cabinets in kitchen, and oak floors throughout. Generously-sized bedrooms and lots of closet space.  Forget about the snow emergencies with the two-car garage.  And, enjoy the neighborliness and the great Mac-Groveland community.

Asking price is $354,900.  We will consider your best and highest offer.  

This property is for-sale-by-owner.  Buyer agent fees will be considered.

Inquiries and offers considered by email at bobtracy@petrognano.net or by phone/text @ 651.329.1794.

description:
Recently sold: $585,000. Exceptional recent new construction on original foundation and a 50 foot wide lot on a fantastic block of Juliet Ave in Mac Groveland!  This beautiful Two Story home was meticulously planned to maximize space and functionality with an open flowing main floor layout, 3 bedrooms on upper level, 3 total bathrooms and a basement roughed in and ready for your finishes!

Highlights of this home include real Acacia hardwood floors, Andersen windows,  LP Smartsiding, Quartz and Carerra surfaces in kitchen and baths, gas fireplace, custom cabinets with easy close doors and drawers and nine foot ceilings on the main floor.  French doors to Juliet balcony in master suite with large soaking tub and heated tile floors and walk in tiled shower in Master bath. 
Enjoy socializing with your neighbors on the huge open front porch, or go relax in your private backyard getaway with gardens, paver patio and gas firepit!

Don't miss this one!!!

description: Recently sold: $249,251. Classic Craftsman Bungalow in an excellent Mac-Groveland Neighborhood! Original woodwork and detail remain throughout, while tasteful updates make for comfortable modern living. The main level features a spacious front porch, plus an open floor-plan with an informal dining room off the kitchen. An updated full bathroom, newer furnace, and restored windows make for stress-free living! Upper level features new paint and carpet, and is a perfect flex area for an office/playspace/studio! The original hardwood floors, and a built-in buffet give the home great character. Enjoy a fully fenced yard, 1-car garage with extra off-street parking, and a patio for barbecuing! HUGE unfinished basement (800+ square feet) with tall ceilings; Add another bedroom, another bathroom, a family room, or all 3! It is rare to get into this neighborhood at this price point...here, you have enough room to build your own equity AND memories.

Recently sold: $425,000. Location location Tangletown! Walk to Grand & Macalester College. This Tudor Duplex is on a large lot perfect for owner occupied or investor. Hardwood floors and fireplaces. Basement has 1/2 bath with additional expansion potential. New boiler, separate electric & heat for both units.

Recently sold: $389,000. Great home! Shiny Hardwood floors, beautiful large new kitchen & inf dr. added on to main floor and patio access. Upstairs finished into large master bedroom, office and sitting room. Rare 2 car garage in back! Convenient location!

description: Recently sold: $518,000. Grand 2 1/2 story steps to Victoria's crossing ??? truly in the heart of Crocus Hill. Meticulously maintained by the same owners for 30+ years. Beautiful hardwood floors, original woodwork & leaded windows throughout. Original wood burning fire place in hearth entry room. Stunning LR & DR with bay windows & built-ins. Amazing upper level master suite with FP + 2 spacious bedrooms with large closet. Finished third level family room with office space and enormous cedar closet for storage! Great deck, yard & 2 car garage. Updated electrical & plumbing. Walk to everything Crocus Hill has to offer ??? shopping & dining is just out your front door! Perfect fit for someone who wants a forever home!

Recently sold: $194,727. Historic Grand Avenue Stunner. Classic Charmer with modern open floor plan and luxury updates. 
LOCATION- Walk to get your coffee, wine, grocery, nails done and yoga class. With a bus stop on the same block as well as uber at the ready, you will not need a car living here! If you do however, on street parking abundant and convenient. Off street parking spot rental available through third party. 
SAFE- Locked back gate entrance. Locked building entrance and locked front door. If you rent a garage you can go from your condo to car in a fully secured environment. The unit is considered "first floor & half" There is another full living level below this with units. The windows are very high from the ground and not possible to access from outside without a ladder. 
LOW ASSOCIATION- 145 a month association will take care of your garbage, heat (glorious steam heat, your skin & hair will thank you come January) water and all maintenance outside your condo.
ALL THE FIXINGS- Dishwasher, garbage disposal, oven, fridge, microwave, included mounted custom gray TV (to match walls) Dual washer & Drier stack IN UNIT! 
CLASSIC BROWNSTONE CHARM REVAMPED- Classic charm meets fresh modern colors and fixtures. Original stain glass accent windows, operating slate OPERATING FIREPLACE, original and professionally refinished hardwood floors. New high end creamy white ceramic floors in both bathroom and kitchen, new granite counter tops through out, classic subway tiled backslash & shower,  brand new vanity, toilet and huge kitchen sink. Fabulous crystal light fixture in kitchen. All cabinets professionally painted an airy white and sealed.
STURDY BUILDING- The building has a new water heater & boiler and front porches recently redone. The roof is in fabulous shape. There are no assessments pending. 
STORAGE GALORE- HUGE, storage space in lower level just for you. Will fit your bikes, skis and more all neatly and with two large egress windows, a secure lock and a built in shelving and hooks. Make it into a wine room, a dark room for photography or a craft area. This footage NOT included in the home square footage. 
FLOOR PLAN- Open where you want it to be but still with a sense of space. The bedroom is closed off from the open kitchen, with a sit up bar and living room area. The brand new completely redone bathroom is not on suite, making it perfect for when guests are over. The ceilings and windows are very tall. The environment is very peaceful and airy.

Highly sought after location, price-point (*Sold for $185,000 in 2000 PRIOR to renovations) and a low inventory market. This home will move quickly. 2.5% commission for buyer agents. Call today to schedule a showing!
Recently sold: $500,000.

description: Recently sold: $330,000. Captivating two-story home, just one block from Mattocks Park! Gleaming hardwood floors beckon you through the front door into the spacious living room. The living room is accented with a wood-burning fireplace, and the adjacent formal dining room is perfect for entertaining thanks to its size. Head through the French doors to the spacious deck overlooking the back yard, or relax with a good book in the daylight filled sunroom. The roomy kitchen features durable porcelain floors, abundant storage, and stainless steel appliances. Three wonderfully quiet  bedrooms can be found on the upper level. They share a full bath that was updated in 2012 with a granite-topped vanity. This home's backyard is expansive and full of perennial plantings to enjoy throughout the warm months. A detached two car garage, new in 2007, will protect your cars and toys from the elements year round. Fantastic location, near shops and restaurants, and a short drive to either downtown. New boiler in 2018!

description: Recently sold: $430,000. Classic Mac-Groveland Charmer - Light streams into the large sunroom, living room, and dining room with an open flow- great for entertaining or being with family. The living room features a gas fireplace with built-in bookshelves opening gracefully to the formal dining room with a long window seat, and a full wall built-in buffet great for displaying treasures and glassware. The kitchen has high-end stainless steel appliances (Bosch dishwasher, Electrolux Gas Range and Microwave), and pull out drawers behind many doors, including the tall pantry. The upstairs has three bedrooms, each with extremely large closets with windows, an updated ceramic bathroom with subway tile, and hardwood floors all around! The lower level has room for a media area, a built-in office area, and a full second bath. The yard includes a two-tier deck, lush landscaping of perennials, and a 2 car garage. Just 5 blocks to the river, 2 blocks to eateries on Grand Ave, and Groveland playground 3 blocks away!

Center hall, huge foyer, large room sizes, amazing original details such as multi-layered crown, wainscoting, large marble fireplace and arched windows. description: Recently sold: $391,251. Truly immaculate 3 BR/ 2 BA 1.5 story home in heart of the Mac-Groveland. Stunning untouched woodwork in the  living & dining room with custom built-ins & beautiful hardwood floors.  Kitchen with granite counter tops, tiled floor & stainless steel appliances & patio doors to great deck. 2 Main floor bedrooms & a full ceramic bath. Upper level master suite with huge walk-in closet & adjustable storage & 3/4 ceramic bath. Skylights with motorized shades provide loads of natural light. Beautiful private fenced back yard with deck. 2-Stall detached garage. Many newer windows, updated furnace, AC, water heater, elec. & plumbing. Within walking distance of Mattocks Park, shopping & restaurants. Live the Saint Paul life at it's finest!  A remarkable place to call home!

description:
Recently sold: $480,000. Welcome home to this classic up/down duplex in the heart of the Mac-Groveland neighborhood! Upper unit features fantastic views/sunsets, 3 bedrooms & 1 bathroom, large kitchen with dishwasher, hardwood floors, spacious living/dining rooms, and lots of natural sunlight! Unit can be partially furnished if desired. Ready to move in & enjoy on April 1st!

Owner pays water, sewer, trash. Tenant pays gas, electric, cable/internet.

For sale: $729,900. Welcome to Crocus Hill's Finest New Listing. Amazing attention to detail on this newly completed remodel of this Colonial Home Offering an Abundance of Living Space. 100% complete remodel both inside and out.  Newly Added 2-Story Addition offers both a Private Master Suite, Upstairs Laundry and Stunning Main Floor Kitchen. Master Bath Features Free Standing Tub, Seperate Shower, Walk-in Closet and Dual Vanities. You'll love all the new upgraded finishes throughout the home and the historic charm. Custom Remodel Includes: Floor to Ceiling Amish Cabinetry with Soft Close, Rollout Garbage, Custom Black Walnut Island Top, Quartz Countertops, Farmhouse Sinks, Brand New SS Appliances and Washer and Dryer, Main Floor Mudroom w/Lockers and Powder Bath, Anderson Windows, New Roof, Matching Doors and Trim to Original Vintage of Home. 4 Bedrooms Upstairs and Lots of Storage in Lower Level.

Recently sold: $315,000. Lovingly cared for and meticulously maintained home in the demand MacGroveland Neighborhood of St. Paul. Updates include newer furnace and central AC, newer windows, and updated electrical and plumbing. Beautiful, original woodwork throughout, wood burning fireplace, and hardwood floors underneath the existing carpet. Sought after layout with living spaces on the main level, including four season porch, and all three bedrooms upstairs. Light and bright, generous closet space, and great potential to finish space in the lower level!
Level lot, fully fenced backyard with patio, plus oversized two car garage. Wonderful location on residential block, close to Groveland Park and Rec Center. A must-see property inside and out!
Recently sold: $415,000.

description: Recently sold: $635,500. Three-story colonial in coveted Kings Maplewood N'hood features 4 bed, 3 bath, 2 car garage. Walking distance to the River Blvd. Home has been extensively remodeled throughout with high-end finishes, including SS appliances, granite, dedicated hot water dispenser, beverage fridge, heated floors on the main (kitchen, family room & bath) & in upper level bath. Large outdoor patio  adjacent to backyard, garage and rear entry. Addition of main floor 1/2 bath, 3rd story expansion, central a/c & 4 zone heating completed and installed as well. Entire house has been nicely updated.. Lower level features media room w/built-in sound & separate wet bar area.

Recently sold: $430,500. Mac-Groveland charm with modern amenities and a surprisingly versatile layout. Totally renovated inside but with much of the original woodwork and charm of a 1926 craftsman bungalow. Open concept kitchen/dining/living/sunroom space, with modern kitchen featuring granite counters and mission-style cabinets. Main level master bedroom with rare full master bath and separate half-bath off living space. Upstairs totally new with 2 bedrooms and full bath. Newly finished basement family room! New Marvin thermal period-look windows and entry doors. Original 1-car garage retained when an oversize 2-car detached garage and backyard fence were added in 2013. Plenty of sheltered off-street parking and storage.

description: Recently sold: $330,000. This updated 1-story St Paul home is filled with historic charm, smart updates and room to expand. A lovingly landscaped front yard greets you as you walk up to the cozy front porch and new front door. Upon entering you'll notice the pride of ownership, hardwood floors and natural light. The updated kitchen is thoughtfully designed with custom cabinets, a dual fuel range and plenty of counter space. The kitchen opens up into the dining room and family room addition, which is filled with windows, light and brand new carpeting. The backyard is the perfect space to entertain featuring a deck, patio, fire pit and lawn. Don't miss the oversized 2 car garage in the back. The basement is dry and currently unfinished, but would be simple to finish to give yourself some instant equity. This home is perfectly located on a quiet dead-end street, and just a short walk to Grand Avenue.

Recently sold: $479,090. Beautifully updated throughout - this Mac Groveland charmer is ready for your family! New kitchen with granite and stainless and new ceramic in both baths will really catch your eye. The bright and open floor plan allows the light to bathe. Enjoy family and friends by the LR fireplace or enjoy coffee and a good book in the 4 season porch. All new floors and paint, including premium carpeting. New roof on both the house and the newly sided 2 car garage! All new windows as well. What a great opportunity for your family to live in this high demand area. Quick closing possible.

description:
Recently sold: $296,232. Charm. Character. Convenience.

Recently sold: $535,000. Discover this enchanting 3-Bedroom, 3-Bath two story gem in a fantastic Mac-Groveland location. Restored original character, and thoughtful, updated touches can be found throughout! The living room is accented with a fireplace, lovely hardwood floors, and is adjacent to the wood-paneled study. A tiled three-quarter bath, a laundry and super storage complete this level. The large back yard is pleasant and private, with a brick patio and gardening space. Two car garage, great location just steps to the river!

description:
Recently sold: $418,000. Remodeled 2 Bedroom in Summit Hill Neighborhood - Another fantastic listing from Chance and Housing Hub! Available for immediate occupancy or a 8/1 move. Location can't be beat in this newly remodeled 2 bedroom/1 bath unit in a duplex. Open concept living space with new gourmet kitchen featuring new stainless steel appliances, stainless steel hood, and dishwasher included. New gas fireplace with gleaming hardwood floors. Plenty of closet space in each bedroom. Extra storage room with washer/dryer included along with utility refrigerator. Single stall parking included. This duplex is quietly nestled on Goodrich Ave just west of Lexington Parkway and 2 blocks south of Grand Ave. Directly across the street from St. Paul Academy with beautiful views of the park. Dining and nightlife options abound just a short walk away. Tenants responsible for all separately metered utilities. Lawn/snow care credit available. Multi year lease preferred. This is a professionally managed home from the folks at Housing Hub. Online access makes applying, paying rent, and scheduling maintenance a breeze. Housing Hub wants to provide you with a great living experience! Mature dogs considered with additional pet deposit and rent. Sorry no cats. Application Criteria:
1. Minimum credit score of 685 or above. 2. Good rental history: No evictions, UDs, or judgments
3. Clean criminal history
4. Income must be 3x the monthly rent No Cats Allowed (RLNE5000336)

description: Recently sold: $490,000.

Recently sold: $326,500. A delightfully charming home set in high-demand Mac Groveland just a short walk to the river parkway and local restaurants and shops. This well-cared for residence has only had 3 owners, and pride of ownership shows in every detail. Features: gleaming hardwood floors, solid oak woodwork and crown molding, fresh paint, lighting updates and newly expanded kitchen cabinets - custom built to match the originals. Lower and upper level spaces hold huge potential for expansion space and equity growth!

Recently sold: $341,000. Welcome home to 432 Hamline Ave. S.! This lovely 1928 bungalow has been updated inside and out and is move-in ready. With 3 bedrooms and 2 baths, modern kitchen, lower level family room and outdoor entertainment spaces, this home is perfect for family living and entertaining.
 
The curb appeal of this home can?t be beat. New landscaping in the front accentuates the lovely architecture found in St. Paul bungalow style homes. As you enter the front door, the beautiful wood burning fireplace will take your breath away. Transom windows, crown molding and 7? baseboards in the living room add elegance to the space. The oak floors throughout the main floor are original to the home.
 
The open floor plan is perfect for entertaining and family living. A wall was opened during a full kitchen remodel in 2010. Great care was taken to retain the historic features of the home, from the design of the arch to the custom cabinets. To add to the function of the space, a breakfast bar was added. Granite countertops, tile backsplash, and high end stainless steel appliances add form and function.
 
The bedrooms on the main floor are spacious and elegantly finished. Crown molding and 7? oak baseboards are painted clean white. The oak floors are original to the home. A main floor bath rounds out the main floor. The lower level is an entertainer?s delight, featuring a large family room with recessed lighting. A spacious bedroom has an egress window and recessed lights. A large, modernly decorated bath features beautiful tile work, double vanity, built in cabinetry and double windows make this bathroom feel large and bright. The unfinished portion of the lower level includes laundry space and mechanicals.
 
The outdoor spaces are ready for play! A large deck and patio are perfect for barbecues and outdoor entertaining. The back yard is surrounded on two sides by a 6? wood fence, and the third side by the garage and a lovely hedge, creating a private retreat. Conveniently located, this home is within walking distance to three parks and two blocks away from Randolph Heights Elementary and Cretin Derham Hall High. Also nearby is shopping, restaurants, and bus.
 
This home has been meticulously maintained, with a new roof and new exterior paint on both the house and garage in 2012. The interior of the home was fully painted in 2011, and the kitchen was remodeled in 2010. The home features hot water heat and has 3 window air conditioners.

description:
Recently sold: $1,030,303. Prairie/Craftsman-influenced, with strong horizontal presence emphasized by roof lines, stucco details outside and plaster and wood features inside.  1.5 size corner lot.  Light-filled with scores of windows, french doors from living room to den, office and dining. 10 rooms on 2 floors + 2.5 baths. First occupied by builder and his family in 1923; he is said to have built it very well, but in deference to his customers, without quite the grandeur of the Summit Av. homes he was building.

Built-in buffet and window seat storage in DR.  Built-in cupboard in den.  Linen closet and cedar closet on 2nd floor.

Kitchen has breakfast area.  New counter tops & sink in 2012, Bosch dishwasher 2011.  Subzero refrigerator, Jenn Air electric convection/radiant oven, Kitchenaid gas range.

New furnace, water heater in '08. Stucco, roof, gutters in 1999-2000.  Front porch and sidewalk redone  in 2012. Basement, once semi-finished, has family room and extra 1/2 bath  but needs redo. Window AC, incl. a 220 v. unit.
